---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout
  title="Driving Distances: km vs Miles"
  description="Quick conversions for road trips across borders. Convert km to miles and miles to km with simple tricks."
  keywords="km to miles, miles to km, driving distance conversion, road trip conversions, kilometers to miles, distance converter"
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Length</span>
      </nav>

      <BlogCrossLinks title="Driving Distances: km vs Miles" />

      <!-- Article Meta -->
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2025-06-13">June 13, 2025</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-300 dark:bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Lead Paragraph -->
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Planning a road trip across borders? If you are driving between metric and imperial countries, you will need to convert distances quickly. Here are the formulas and tricks to keep you oriented.
      </p>

      <!-- Section: The Conversion -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Conversion</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-6 my-6 not-prose shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-center text-xl font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">
          1 mile = 1.609 km | 1 km = 0.621 miles
        </p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">
          Quick trick: miles × 1.6 = km | km × 0.6 = miles
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: The Fibonacci Trick -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">The Fibonacci Trick</h2>
      <p>The ratio between miles and kilometres is remarkably close to the golden ratio (1.618). This means consecutive Fibonacci numbers approximate the conversion:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>5 miles ≈ 8 km (actual: 8.05)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>8 miles ≈ 13 km (actual: 12.87)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>13 miles ≈ 21 km (actual: 20.92)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>21 miles ≈ 34 km (actual: 33.80)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Section: Common Driving Distances -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Common Driving Distances</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Miles</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Kilometres</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Context</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">10</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">16</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Short commute</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">50</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">80</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">City to suburb</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">100</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">161</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Day trip</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">250</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">402</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Long day drive</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">500</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-mono">805</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Major road trip</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Section: Tips -->
      <h2 class="flex items-center gap-3 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Road Trip Tips</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>GPS apps</strong> let you switch units — match it to local road signs</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Fuel planning:</strong> Fill up at distance intervals that make sense in local units</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Border crossings:</strong> Signs switch units immediately — be prepared</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Odometer:</strong> Most cars can toggle between miles and km in settings</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- Converter CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-50 to-orange-50 dark:from-amber-900/20 dark:to-orange-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">
            🔗 Try our free length converter
          </p>
          <a
            href="/convert/length"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Open Converter →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back to Blog -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-amber-500 transition-colors">
          ← Back to all articles
        </a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
